 relevance of the utopian aspirations and formal innovations of the early twentieth century by submitting them to homage and travesty. Sure to set the standard for future studies of Genzken’s work, Isa Genzken is essential for anyone interested in contemporary art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGenzken, Isa,-1948--Criticism and interpretation. 0aSculpture - Germany - 21st century. 0aSculpturezGermanyy20th century. 0aSculpturezGermanyy21st century. 0aSculpture-Germany-20th century. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aIsa Genzken.  aWest Germany.  aarchitecture.  abody.  acommodity.  aperception.  asculpture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226410036423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226410036/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles